  "title": "Author's Postscript",
  "content": "<h1 class=\"heading_1\"><a class=\"heading-link\" href=\"/read/v0/2\">Author&apos;s Postscript</a></h1><hr/><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">THANK YOU VERY much for reading Volume 0.</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">I&#x2019;m Shougo Kinugasa, and my favorite food is ochazuke, my favorite drink is black tea, and my hobby is watching baseball.</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">I&#x2019;ve been itching to get a pet, either a dog or a cat, but every time we take a family vote, it always ends in a two-to-two tie, so we can never make a decision.</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">My recent struggle has been with microwaving frozen pasta. I want it to be piping hot, so I tend to heat it just a little too long. As a result, the noodles dry out, and I end up eating crunchy pasta, which is a constant source of frustration. Even when I try to fine-tune the timing, the result is the same. Is it my fault for not mastering the microwave, or is it the microwave&#x2019;s fault? It&#x2019;s definitely the microwave.</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">&#x2026;Well, enough of my rambling&#x2014;let&#x2019;s move on to discussing Volume 0.</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">This special edition dedicates an entire volume to a forbidden past arc, a somewhat taboo topic within the Classroom of the Elite series. How did you like it?</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">The White Room setting existed as part of the background material when Classroom of the Elite started in 2015, but I never imagined back then that I would one day delve deeper into it and write an entire volume about it.</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">As an author, I&#x2019;m incredibly happy that this could be realized, even in this special form. Completing it without disrupting the regular publication schedule was quite a challenge, but I would be delighted if even one more person enjoys it.</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">Actually, alongside the White Room arc, there&#x2019;s another untold story&#x2014;the &#x201c;Blank Year&#x201d; arc&#x2014;that exists as part of the background material. It covers Ayanokouji Kiyotaka&#x2019;s one-year period between the end of Volume 0 and the beginning of Year 1, Volume 1.</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">At this point, there are no plans to turn this material into a book. However, I&#x2019;ve started to vaguely think that it might be interesting if it could be shaped into something someday.</p><p class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left\">Well then, everyone, it&#x2019;s been short, but I&#x2019;ll take my leave here for now. Let&#x2019;s meet again in the afterword of the main series. See you!</p>",
